[]($section.id('about'))
This is a non-exhaustive, curated list of changes meant to help users quickly see what has improved since they last checked.

You can <a href="index.xml">subscribe to this page via RSS</a>.

[]($section.id('v2.0.0').data('date','2026-04-27'))
# Calculator overhaul, map rewrite, Fish Guide and source-backed data
- Calculator moved to API-backed data and Datastar state
  - Source-backed items, buffs, lightstones, gear effects, pets, pet skills and item/pet icons
  - Saved calculator presets, saved layout presets, pinned sections, share links and searchable selectors
  - Bite Time, Loot Flow, group distribution, silver distribution and Target Fish views
- Map shell and interaction model were rebuilt
  - Movable windows, bookmarks, map presets and persisted UI state
  - Search expressions for fish, zones, grades, favourites, missing fish and patch date ranges
  - Zone catch profile summaries, provenance details and semantic region/territory details
  - 3D mode was removed (for now...)
- Fishydex was expanded
  - Fish Guide view
  - Favourites, progress charts, filters, sorting and details modal
  - Evidence-backed best spot lists
- Data paths moved toward source-backed inputs
  - Original/source files for map layers, item icons, pet icons, localized names and calculator catalogs
  - Provenance markers for zone loot and fish evidence data where available
- Site localization was rebuilt around Fluent
  - German UI work
  - Korean data-name support
  - Translation fallback notices and profile language settings
- Hosting/deployment changed direction
  - Self-hosted services instead of relying on Fly.io
  - Nix/mgmt service bundles for API, Dolt, CDN, edge and opt-in telemetry services
  - Grafana, Jaeger, Loki, Prometheus and Vector observability plumbing

[]($section.id('v1.0.0').data('date','2026-03-15'))
# Interactive Map, data pipeline, Fishydex and complete site overhaul
- Beautiful new illustrations thanks to Baklow 🤩
- New Bevy-powered map built from scratch with 
  - Zone and Region Group masks
  - Search feature
  - Fish Evidence Points (exact locations where people actually caught specific fish 😉)
- Fishydex index for tracking your fish guide progress
- Calculator cleanup with regrouped controls, improved catch-time/session panels
- New API backend for fish, zones, region groups and other layers, fish evidence events
- Site polish across the homepage, guides, devlog timeline, and shared layouts, plus a lot of legacy CSS and old code removed

The map is still in a pretty rough state right now (please do not try 3D mode).
Since is is run as single threaded WASM app, it might also suffer heavily from performance issues.

But I'd rather have things available already and continuously improve it. So here we go :)
I will try to push some fixes after doing profiling work.

[]($section.id('v0.2.0').data('date','2025-10-04'))
# Website touch up
- General Layout improvements to display more adequate data
- Groundwork done for a Multilingual Website
- DaisyUI + tailwindcss with theme selector

I've finally found some time to do a much needed overhaul.
I do hope the new page layout system will be useful to you.

We also now have the ability to mirror pages to their translated counter-parts. 
So if there is strong demand for a specific language we can hopefully make it happen.

Volunteer work very welcome :)

[]($section.id('v0.1.0').data('date','2025-03-23'))
# Beta Pre-Release
- hello world :)
- Things will definitely still change

